      <h2 class="pml-50__title">How does MCP work? </h2>
      
      <div class="pml-50__desc text">
          <p>MCP is built on a client → model → server architecture: </p>
<ul><li>The <b>Client</b> gathers context (user info, role, task, environment). </li><li>The <b>Model</b> (e.g., Claude, GPT) receives the context and a list of available tools or actions. </li><li>The <b>Server</b> hosts the tools (APIs, databases, etc.) and executes any actions the model requests. </li></ul>
<p>All communication follows <b>structured schemas</b> so everything is interpretable, traceable, and secure. </p>

      </div>
      <div class="pml-50__cta-wrapper">
        <a href="https://www.avaya.com/en/documents/wp-model-context-protocol-uc16044en.pdf" class="pml-50__primary-btn" rel="noreferer, noopener" target="_blank">
          <span>Read the white paper</span>
        </a>
        
      </div>
